Design and développementLe S. 22 is a plane single-seater, twin-engine, biplane. Its two engines Isotta Fraschini V. 6bis of 300 hp and are mounted on eight struts between the hull and the wing top, in Push-pull configuration.Aviation: RAIS seaplane race
History opérationnelleAu during test flights over Lake Maggiore before the Trophy Schneider 1921, the S. 22 crashed in the lake, putting an end to the hope to see him represent Italy in the competition.Aviation: RAIS seaplane race
